—limit new reprocessing capacity to that required for breeders, and limit
                        separation of plutonium to avoid unnecessary stockpiling and pressure for
                        thermal recycle;

—agree to US consent rights, as called for in
                        the NNPA, including their continuation
                        over material after use in breeder RD&D programs;

—adopt predictable ground rules for exercise of consent rights over
                        reprocessing and plutonium use in specified breeder and other advanced
                        reactor RD&D programs;
